title: Newly Single Kaley Cuoco Adopts New Puppy, Chester
text:
Comments Cuoco shared two photos of her and her newly adopted puppy, named Chester, on her Instagram page. 
Having already had a number of puppies, Kaley Cuoco has adopted another one which she named Chester Cuoco. The adoption came in the wake of her separation from estranged husband Ryan Sweeting. On Friday, October 23, Cuoco took to Instagram to keep her followers updated on her new four-legged companion. The newly single actress and animal lover shared an adorable snap of herself wearing a blue ball cap and sitting on a couch while holding the new addition to the family. "Welcome to the family Chester Cuoco!!!! thank you @pawworks #couldnthelpmyself #savethemall #iblamemymomforshowingmehispicture @peteyleo," she wrote alongside the image. A photo posted by @normancook on Oct 23, 2015 at 12:55pm PDT Cuoco also shared on her Instagram page another photo of her hugging Chester as she offered wide smile to the camera. "Chester!!!! @pawworks," she captioned it, tagging Paw Works, an animal rescue located in Los Angeles. Chester will join a growing family of dogs that Cuoco has already had, one of which is her famous pit mix Norman. A photo posted by @normancook on Oct 23, 2015 at 5:28pm PDT
